1. The earliest psychologists studied the human mind using introspection. Would this be a good way to inform efforts in
AI to model human cognitive processes?

Since introspection relies exclusively on observation of one's own conscious thought, feelings and human self-reflection, and not mediated by other sources of knowledge,
it might be good for AI model human cognitive processes. Introspection considering individuals' unique experience as the determinants of mental 
state, machine learning process for AI is a process of cummulating knowledge and experiences for a machine which is also considering unique experience of the machine 
to model human cognitive proceeses.
